# PR & Code Review

## Opening a PR
- Keep it **small and focused** (one logical change). Break up large work.
- Reference the relevant task and **acceptance criteria** in the description ([`.plan/`](../../.plan/) sprint files).
- Template:

```md
## What / Why
<change and rationale>

## Related task
.plan/sprint-XX-.../NN-...-tasks.md → <epic/task>

## Testing
<unit/integration/e2e + coverage note>

## Checklist
- [ ] DoD met  - [ ] i18n (en-US + tr-TR)  - [ ] CI green
```

## Merge prerequisites
- All CI gates green: `lint → i18n-check → unit-test → integration-test → coverage-gate → build → image-build`.
- At least **1 approval**; changes affecting architecture require **Tech Lead approval**.
- [`.plan/definition-of-done.md`](../../.plan/definition-of-done.md) §1 must be satisfied.

## Reviewer checklist
- Scope: does the change match the brief/sprint goal? (no scope creep — [`.plan/project-brief.md`](../../.plan/project-brief.md) §7)
- Correctness + test adequacy (thresholds: core ≥80%, critical ≥90%).
- i18n: no hardcoded text, both locales complete.
- Security: input validation, authorization, no secret leakage, no path traversal/SSRF.
- Code style ([`code-standards.mdc`](./code-standards.mdc)) and module boundaries.

## Etiquette
- Constructive, concrete feedback; prefix minor suggestions with "nit:".
- On rejected/failed CI, add a **new commit** (no amend); no force-push after review.
